President Obama had a video teleconference with President Karzai, discussing topics such as the transition to Afghan security lead, the renewal of the U.S.-Afghanistan Strategic Partnership Declaration, and U.S. troop reductions in July. They agreed to work together for a political outcome in Afghanistan and emphasized the importance of resolving issues with Kabul Bank. President Obama expressed regret for a tragic accident in Kunar Province and both leaders acknowledged that such incidents undermine their efforts in fighting terrorism. President Obama also had a meeting with his national security team, discussing regional diplomatic efforts, security situations, and the transition process in Afghanistan.